bugs.description: Undefined variable '_trace' used on line 124. The function expr() calls _trace.get_obj_expr(ref) but _trace is not imported anywhere in the file. This will cause a NameError when the expr() function is called.

Undefined variable '_ops' used on line 136. The function from_pandas() calls _ops.pandas_to_awl(df) but _ops is not imported anywhere in the file. This will cause a NameError when the from_pandas() function is called.

Comparison with None using '==' instead of 'is' on line 72. The code uses 'if row == None:' which should be 'if row is None:' according to Python best practices. Using '==' with None can lead to unexpected behavior if the object has a custom __eq__ method.
Incorrect return type annotation on line 36. The function model_to_str() is annotated to return Table but actually returns str (from table_to_str()). The return type should be 'str' not 'Table'.
